{
  "texts": [
    "The creation of formal energy-aware models for federated Cloud-Edge systems is a challenging task due to a lack of empirical data to calculate stochastic properties, a lack of analysis to model geographical energy distribution factors such as supply and demand of green and brown energy sources, a limited understanding of temporal energy pricing, and limited modeling of energy provider policies & restrictions.",
    "To address this, empirical data must be assessed across a range of disciplines, and appropriate model types identified for each sub-system.",
    "How to combine models?Once models for each sub-system in an energy-aware Cloud-Edge infrastructure have been created, there are still significant challenges with regard to integrating these models.",
    "These challenges include how to best integrate different model types (e.g.",
    "a graph-based model integrating with a model based on queuing theory), how to determine appropriate granularities when simulating the models, how to mathematically reason across the combined model, etc."
  ]
}